[[File:Jasmínová, lavička a klepadlo.jpg|thumb|A carpet hanger in [[Prague]]]] [[File:Ignacy Płażewski, Bloki mieszkaniowe na osiedlu Włady Bytomskiej w Łodzi, I-4710-14.jpg|thumb|Children playing at a carpet hanger, [[Łódź]], ca. 1960s]] The outdoor '''carpet hanger''' (also '''carpet stand''' or '''carpet rack''') is a construction to hang carpets for cleaning with the help of [[carpet beater]]s. It is known in Germany, Poland, Lithuania, the Czech Republic, Finland,<ref name=rii>[http://www.polarinertia.com/apr12/carpet01.htm "Carpet Racks in Finland"], by Riitta Oittinen</ref> Russia, and other countries.
==Secondary usage== It was a small center of social life.<ref>[http://naukawpolsce.pap.pl/aktualnosci/news,406674,socjolog-dla-wielu-nastolatkow-galerie-handlowe-to-wspolczesne-podworka.html Socjolog: dla wielu nastolatków galerie handlowe to współczesne podwórka]</ref> German writers [[Walter Benjamin]] and [[Erich Kästner]] described hangers as important places during their childhood.<ref>Thomas Blubacher, ''Wie es einst war: Schönes und Wissenswertes aus Großmutters Zeiten''</ref> Children may use it as a playground, as a soccer goal, as a drumming implement, etc.<ref>[http://klaipeda.diena.lt/naujienos/lietuva/salies-pulsas/uzkliuvo-kilimu-dulkinimo-stovas-537077 "Užkliuvo kilimų dulkinimo stovas"]</ref>
