[[File:Velleman-MK139-clap-on-off-switch.jpg|thumb|125px|alt=A photo of a Velleman clap on/off switch electronic project printed circuit board|A Velleman clap-activated on/off switch electronic project]]{{about|the electronics company|the surname|Velleman (surname)}}
'''Velleman''' is a Belgian producer and distributor of electronics, in particular for hobbyists. In a blog post introducing the products, [[RadioShack]] claimed Velleman to be "the undisputed leader in do-it-yourself kits and components".<ref>{{cite web|title=Build something cool with Velleman kits at RadioShack|url=http://blog.radioshack.com/2011/06/11/build-something-cool-with-velleman-kits-at-radioshack/#more-157|accessdate=December 11, 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809082219/http://blog.radioshack.com/2011/06/11/build-something-cool-with-velleman-kits-at-radioshack|date=June 11, 2011|archive-date=August 9, 2011 |deadurl=yes}}</ref>
The company was founded in 1975<ref>[http://www.facebook.com/pages/Velleman-nv/211574802193671 Facebook page]; read December 11, 2011. The company profile only says the 1970s.</ref> as a family-owned maker of [[do it yourself|do-it-yourself]] electronic kits, and incorporated as Velleman NV in the 1980s. It is headquartered in [[Gavere]] in [[East Flanders]], 10&nbsp;km south-west of [[Ghent]], has 165 employees worldwide and a [[revenue|turnover]] of 37 million euros (2009).<ref>[http://www.ibs.net/fr/resources/case-studies/IBS-simplifie-la-logistique-chez-Velleman/ IBS simplifie la logistique chez Velleman] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120110181716/http://www.ibs.net/fr/resources/case-studies/IBS-simplifie-la-logistique-chez-Velleman/ |date=2012-01-10 }}, press release from IBS, posted April 22, 2010; read December 11, 2011.</ref>
